class Solution {
    public int singleNumber(int[] nums) {
        int result=0;
        for( int num:nums){
            result=result^num;
        }
        return result;
    }
    
}

SO why i choose XOR means,the XOR operator cancels out duplicate numbers because a ^ a = 0.
By XORing all elements in the array, the pairs become zero.
The remaining value is the number that appears only once.
